      "message": "I try and think about leading/trailing and left/right as different coordinate spaces. Edge insets may need to be in either one, depending on how they will be used -- for example, insets for a flippable UI element are in leading/trailing space, but the safe area insets are for the absolute coordinates of the hardware. Because the UIEdgeInsets data structure is left/right, the only way to handle it is to always assume it\u0027s in the absolute coordinate space and convert out when assigning to leading/trailing values (and that means you need to convert into left/right when assigning from leading/trailing into a UIEdgeInsets).",
